HEADWORD: Extensibility
<hw>Ex*ten`si*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
of being extensible; the capacity of being extended; <as>as, the
<ex>extensibility</ex> of a fiber, or of a plate of
metal</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extensible</ent>⟦br⟧
